title: Tigerhawks take a set, lose to Warhawks
text:
Tigerhawks take a set, lose to Warhawks Published: Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015 11:21 a.m. CDT By Troy Hyde Newton Daily News 
NEW SHARON — Taking a set from North Mahaska inside its home gym gave Colfax-Mingo’s volleyball team plenty of confidence heading into the rest of the match. 
North Mahaska squashed the Tigerhawks’ momentum with a win in the third set and then closed out the four-set win with a narrow advantage in the fourth set. 
The Warhawks remained in third place in the South Iowa Cedar League following a 25-21, 13-25, 25-19, 25-23 victory on Monday. 
The match featured Colfax-Mingo sophomore Ries Wilson and North Mahaska’s Olivia Boender, who are third and fourth, respectively, in kills in the SICL. 
Wilson did her part for the Tigerhawks, collecting 20 kills. She had nine digs, three aces and two blocks. She currently ranks third in the league with 219 kills and fifth in digs with 205. 
Megan Earles surpassed 300 assists on the season as she finished with 24 assists in the match. She ranks third in the SICL with 315 assists. 
Aranda Woods contributed six kills against the Warhawks, while Dakota Hostetter chipped in four kills and seven digs. Chelsea Russell recorded 22 digs and three aces. 
Colfax-Mingo fell to 5-15 on the season and 3-7 in conference play. North Mahaska entered the match with losses in four of its five previous matches but improved to 17-10 overall and 8-2 in SICL play. 
Colfax-Mingo plays in another SICL match at 7:30 p.m. Thursday in Keota. It travels to the Woodward-Granger tourney on Saturday.
